The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, January 04, 2004 				 ETC merger swap ratio fixed at 3:1
																								Mumbai, Jan. 3 (PTI): The boards of ETC Networks and Econnect India  both subsidiaries of Zee Telefilms  have approved the proposal to merge the two companies and a share swap ratio of three Econnect India shares for every ETC Networks share of Rs 10 each.																								However, to rationalise the resultant share capital of Econnect India (merged entity), the share capital of Econnect India would be re-organised by consolidating three shares into one equity share, ETC Networks, a Zee group company, informed the Bombay Stock Exchange today.																								Therefore, upon completion of amalgamation and capital re-organisation of the company and Econnect India, shareholders the company would be issued and allotted one equity share of Econnect India for every equity share held by them, ETC Networks said.																								The name of the merged entity would be changed to ETC Networks Ltd and the merger process is expected to be completed within four to five months.																								The proposed merger is subject to the approval of shareholders of the company and the high courts of Mumbai and Delhi, it added.
